---
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import AdSlot from "../../../components/AdSlot.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Infra Cost Recovery - Use Case | SaaS Pricing Toolkit"
  description="A simple flow for pricing infra-heavy features: bandwidth + storage cost estimation, then pricing at target margin."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Use case: infra cost recovery</h1>
    <p>
      This flow helps you back into pricing for bandwidth- and storage-heavy features while keeping margins predictable.
    </p>
    <div class="btn-row">
      <a class="btn primary" href="/saas-pricing/bandwidth-cost-calculator/">Start with bandwidth</a>
      <a class="btn ghost" href="/saas-pricing/">Back to toolkit</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grid">
    <section class="card col8">
      <h2>Recommended steps</h2>
      <ol class="list">
        <li>
          Estimate egress cost and a recommended price:{" "}
          <a href="/saas-pricing/bandwidth-cost-calculator/">bandwidth cost calculator</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          Add storage and request costs: <a href="/saas-pricing/storage-cost-calculator/">storage cost calculator</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          Convert fixed overhead to a per-unit price:{" "}
          <a href="/saas-pricing/usage-based-pricing-calculator/">usage-based pricing calculator</a>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Notes</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Use average monthly storage (GB-month), not peak storage.</li>
        <li>If you have tiered egress pricing, use an average blended cost per GB.</li>
        <li>Keep a fixed overhead bucket for monitoring, support, and baseline infra.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <aside class="card col4">
      <h2>Good for</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>CDN-backed media features</li>
        <li>Data retention add-ons</li>
        <li>Backup/export capabilities</li>
      </ul>
      <AdSlot slot="5031589887" containerStyle="margin-top: 1rem;" />
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
